<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-3687] Local range scans are not run on the read stage</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-3687</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Running directly on the client request/StorageProxy thread means we&apos;re now allowing one range scan per thrift thread instead of one per read stage thread &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;which may be more, or less, depending on thrift server mode&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;, and it bypasses the &quot;drop hopeless requests&quot; overcapacity protection built in there. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12536810">CASSANDRA-3687</key>
            <summary>Local range scans are not run on the read stage</summary>
